subtitle: When to get medical help
title: Warning signs
content:
Created by BabyCenter

There are many changes to your body in pregnancy, and it is normal to wonder if you need to worry about any of these changes.

**This is normal**: Are you tired, feeling nauseous in the mornings, getting indigestion, and having to urinate more often?, Is your skin changing? Are you feeling breathless? Welcome to pregnancy! 

**These are warning signs**: See a doctor or midwife if you have any of these feelings:

•	Pain in your belly

•	A fever

•	Blurred vision and you are seeing spots in front of your eyes

•	Fluid leaking from your vagina

•	Pain when urinating

•	If you are past 5 months in your pregnancy, and your baby has stopped kicking or is kicking much less

•	If you have heavy bleeding or bleeding with pain.
